> Run hdparm -tT /dev/hd? to time the speed of the buffer cache as well as the
> transfer speed. The latter will be corrected by the result of the first.
Yep, that worked:
 Timing buffer-cache reads:   32 MB in  0.42 seconds =76.19 MB/sec
 Timing buffered disk reads:  16 MB in  2.56 seconds = 6.25 MB/sec
And this is stable for -tT.
